<h3 class="date"><a href="/2007/oct/26/">&#x27a0;</a> October 26, 2007</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="apple-yanks-wireless-backup" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.appleinsider.com/articles/07/10/26/apple_yanks_wireless_backup_from_leopard_last_minute.html">AppleInsider | Apple yanks wireless backup from Leopard last minute</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Wow, I hadn&#8217;t noticed this had gone.</p>

<p>Digging deeper, it appears that you can only use Time Machine to backup to network drives shared using &#8220;Apple File Protocol&#8221;, rather than the more common SMB.  Glad I have my Drobo hooked up to a Mac Mini, because that&#8217;s one of the main reasons I bought it.</p>

