<h3 class="date"><a href="/2007/aug/19/">&#x27a0;</a> August 19, 2007</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    <div class="flickrentry entry">
        <h4>3953 mAh</h4>

        <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/groovymother/1171053265/"><img class="flickrphoto" alt="3953 mAh" src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1043/1171053265_59c472a3a6_m.jpg" height="240" width="155" /></a>

        <p>
            <p>Ouch!  My MacBookPro's battery capacity has dropped to 71% -- but it was at 98-ish% before I left for this trip and used my laptop on battery power on the airplane and yesterday at BarCampBlock.</p>

<p>I suspect that I should be able to get the battery replaced at the Apple Store under warranty -- 30% capacity drop after 17 loadcycles doesn't sound right at all.</p>
        </p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
                    Filed under
                    
